text: The Ruahine is a mountain range in the North Island of New Zealand. Ruahine may also refer to: * Ruahine (New Zealand electorate), a former New Zealand parliamentary electorate * Ruahine Albert, a New Zealand anti-domestic violence activist * MS Ruahine, a passenger ship built in 1950 * SS Ruahine, a passenger ship built in 1909 * Ruahine Fault, a geological fault in the North Island Fault System, New Zealand ==See also== * Ngāruahine, a Māori iwi located in South Taranaki, North Island, New Zealand
title: Ruahine (disambiguation)
